UTM ZONE is a segment of the Earths surface 6 degrees of longitude in width. The zones are numbered eastward starting at the meridian 180 degrees from the prime meridian at Greenwich. There are five zones numbered 7 through 11 that cover British Columbia
column5: Zone 10 with a central meridian at -123 degrees.

description: UTM EASTING is the distance in meters eastward to or from the central meridian of a UTM zone with a false easting of 500000 meters. e.g.

column4: uniquely identifies a single flow line such that a main channel and a secondary channel with the same watershed code would have different blue line keys (the Fraser River and all side channels have different blue line keys).

description: From BC FWA
